title: Microsoft Case Poses Test for FTC's Fight Against 'Vertical' Mergers
description: The antitrust-enforcement agency seeks to block the Activision purchase with arguments similar to those that have failed in the past.

title: NASA Prepares for Orion Spacecraft Splashdown to Conclude Artemis I Mission
description: The agency will attempt to return part of the Orion spacecraft to Earth on Sunday, a maneuver that will expose the vehicle to heat approaching 5,000 degrees after a nearly monthlong journey.

title: Sam Bankman-Fried Set to Testify to Congress About FTX Collapse
description: FTX founder Sam Bankman-Fried said that he would testify next week before Congress, setting up a high-profile exchange with lawmakers.

title: I Entered a Pun Competition. My Jokes Were Written by an AI Chatbot.
description: ChatGPT, a trendy new artificial intelligence robot, can generate all sorts of writing. But is it punny?

title: Microsoft Faces Tougher Path to Closing Activision Deal
description: The software giant should give up on the deal, some analysts say, following the FTC’s challenge to block the $75 billion bid

title: Former Apple Executive Says Company Blundered by Firing Him After TikTok Video
description: The tech giant, which is grappling with supply delays in China, has lost top negotiator Tony Blevins, who says he was quoting a movie when he made a joke on video at a car show.

title: Workers at GM-LG Battery Plant in Ohio Vote to Unionize
description: The result is a win for the UAW, which plans organizing campaigns at many U.S. battery factories slated to open in coming years.

title: Google Ad Software Disrupted for Publishers Large and Small
description: The malfunction, which lasted more than 2½ hours, affected software that places digital ads on websites.
